            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ye shall not see wind",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The verb ‘see’ is used elsewhere of what is not visible but experienced by the other senses. So ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 20:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘All the people ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "saw",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the thunderings … and the noise of the trumpet’. After a drought wind is in the East the general precursor of rain. Cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 18:41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
